    <section id="fs-id1167066953844" class="summary">
      <title>Section Summary</title>
      <list id="fs-id1167063801721">
        <item>The six types of simple machines make work easier by changing the <emphasis>f</emphasis><emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis> term so that force is reduced at the expense of increased distance. </item>
        <item>The ratio of output force to input force is a machine’s mechanical advantage.</item>
        <item>Combinations of two or more simple machines are called complex machines.</item>
        <item>The ratio of output work to input work is a machine’s efficiency.</item>

      </list>
    </section>
